bugs.title: CVE-2019-19601 texlive: buffer overflow in the TexOpen() function in detex.l

bugzilla.short_desc: CVE-2019-19601 texlive: buffer overflow in the TexOpen() function in detex.l

long_desc.thetext:
OpenDetex 2.8.5 has a Buffer Overflow in TexOpen in detex.l because of an incorrect sprintf.

Upstream Issue:

https://github.com/pkubowicz/opendetex/issues/60

Created texlive tracking bugs for this issue:

Affects: fedora-all [bug 1798119]

Statement:

This flaw only affects the detex binary, which is not provided by any versions of texlive as shipped with Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7 and 8.
Closing this flaw as NOTABUG as the affected function is only used within detex binary, which is not shipped with any RHEL's texlive version.
